726258f-a.title: Queens: Broadway - Elmhurst Avenue
726258f-a.text:
Broadway, north side, east from Elmhurst to Whitney Avenues.
At the latter avenue is the Long Island Railroad trestle.
P. L. Sperr  April 25, 1936
NO REPPODUCTIONS

726529f-a.title: Queens: Elmhurst Avenue - Broadway
726529f-a.text:
20 Elmhurst Avenue, adjoining the NVW. corner of Broadway,
showing an old mansion. According to Mr. Beecher the house was
built by Samuel Lord of Lord and Taylor, fashionable New York
department store, as a wedding gift for his daughter Elizabeth
(Mrs. Warren) and was known as the ''Lord House' and the ''Warren
House.'' It has also been known as the ''Combes House'' for many
years, after Dr. Combes.
Gift of Beecher Ogden  1941
NO REPRODUCTIONS
